relationship.description:
Moving from OPA to NEMO:
- see http://www.nemo-ocean.eu/About-NEMO/Reference-manuals for more details
The main modifications from OPA v8 and NEMO/OPA v3.2 and relevant for coupling with AGCMs are : 
1. transition to full native FORTRAN90, deep code restructuring and drastic reduction of CPP keys ; 
2. introduction of partial step representation of bottom topography [Barnier et al. 2006, Le Sommer et al. 2009, Penduff et al. 2007] ; 
3. additiona lschemes for vector and flux forms of the momentum advection;
4. additional advection schemes for tracers;
5. online diagnostics:tracers trend in the mixed layer and vorticity balance;
6. rewriting of the I/O management with the use of an I/O server;
7. generalized ocean-ice-atmosphere-CO2 coupling interface, interfaced with OASIS 3 coupler ;
8. surface module (SBC) that simplify the way the ocean is forced and include two bulk formulea (CLIO and CORE) and which includes an on-the-fly interpolation of input forcing fields ;
9. RGB light penetration and optional use of ocean color
10. major changes in the TKE schemes : it now includes a Langmuir cell parameterization [Axell 2002], the Mellor and Blumberg [2004] surface wave breaking parameterization, and has a time discretization which is energetically consistent with the ocean model equations [Burchard 2002, Marsaleix et al. 2008] ;
11. tidal mixing parametrisation (bottom intensification) + Indonesian specific tidal mixing [Koch-Larrouy et al. 2007] ;
